# Development Lifecycle

## Stages

```
IDEA → DRAFT → PLAN → IMPLEMENT → VERIFY → MERGE → (RELEASE)
```

### Draft
A raw idea or bug added with `/draft` → `docs/specs/backlog/`. Minimal — just capture it.

### Plan
`/plan {id}` turns a draft into a ready spec in one light pass: a goal, **observable acceptance criteria**, an approach + interfaces, and subtasks. It surfaces open questions (batched up front when you pass multiple IDs) and defaults to keeping work in scope — deferrals are the exception and get noted. Spec moves to `docs/specs/ready/`.

### Implement
`/implement {id}`: for each subtask, write the code and its tests, run the fast gate (`scripts/ci.sh fast` via the `runner` agent), and commit green. The spec's checkboxes + git log are the progress record — `/resume` reconstructs from them after any interruption.

### Verify
`/verify` at feature-done: the full gate (`ci.sh full` — all automated tests + build), a review (inline self-review by default; the `reviewer` agent or `/consult` only for critical changes), and — for new features — a blackbox manual smoke test (the `smoke-tester` agent drives the app from explicit steps, reports failures only). Every smoke-found bug becomes an automated test.

### Merge
**Local git, no formal PR** (default): fast-forward + gate-already-green-on-this-HEAD → `git merge --ff-only`, no re-run; otherwise resolve conflicts locally, re-run `ci.sh full`, then merge. Use `/pr` only for external review / repos that require it.

### Release
`/release patch|minor|major`: bump version + changelog (main session), then `scripts/release.sh` runs the gate + build/publish/deploy locally (via the `runner`); GitHub Actions release only as a fallback.

`/ship` orchestrates the whole chain from a spec list or a topic.

---

## Parallel Sessions

Run multiple sessions **on different branches**. State lives in the repo (branch + spec checkboxes + git log), so sessions on different branches never conflict. Don't run two sessions on the same branch (they'd race on the same files). One session per branch.

---

## Branching

This project uses: **{{BRANCHING_MODEL}}**

| Branch | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `feature/feat-001-title` | one per spec |
| `fix/bug-042-title` | bug fixes |

- Push feature branches freely (backup). The quality gate is local (`/verify`) before the merge.
- **main-only:** feature branches merge into `main`; `/release` tags on `main`.
- **git-flow:** feature branches merge into `develop`; `/release` runs the full gate on `develop`, merges `develop → master`, and tags — `master`'s tip is always the latest release.
